how soon after chilbirth can i return to school i recently asked for advice about an unplanned pregnancy and everyone was so helpful that now i'm wondering with an average i know haha labor how long would it be before a woman could return to college classes student teaching for those of you with children how long would it have did it take you you see i'm as stubborn determined as a boar and i'm wondering is there any chance it could be within two weeks or is that all urban legend about people who do that i had my daughter when i was in high school and went back after just two weeks it is different for everyone but go back when you feel ready for some it takes longer it has a lot to do with how labor and delivery went if it kicked your butt then you might need a little down time or if you had a csection it might take a little longer to get back into the swing of things another thing to consider is how much rest are you and your baby getting and who will care for the child while you are away good luck and congrats Pregnancy Premature birth Episodes of Lost (Season 1) Breastfeeding Childbirth The Apprentice 2 Breech birth Pitaten Similarities between the Bible and the Qur'an Avenue Q American football Social rule Abortion debate Columbia University Boston Public Melanie Wilkes Current teachings of Prem Rawat Education in Germany Incarnations of Immortality University of Waterloo Knots Landing Graduate school Kodocha Obstetrics Jon Secada Urinary incontinence The Lion, the Witch and the Wardrobe Cornell University Psoriasis The Family from One End Street Futurama (TV series - season 2) Hiberno-English Blood on the Tracks Love Hina main characters Sex education Laura Schlessinger Education in the People's Republic of China History of As the World Turns (2000-present) Culture of the United States Fertility awareness Characters of Lost Swami Vivekananda Economic inequality Working time Aerial (dance move) Beavis and Butt-head Professional wrestling attacks Prenatal diagnos